  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study seeks to assess the virologic effectiveness of dual therapy (lopinavir/ ritonavir
      (LPV/r) + lamivudine (3TC)) in treatment-experienced human immunodeficiency virus 1 (HIV-1)
      infected participants with an undetectable plasma HIV-1 (ribonucleic acid) RNA level (for at
      least 6 months) at the 48 week time point of treatment in the routine clinical settings of
      the Russian Federation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
